            <summary>
              <p>François Déroche schreibt zum Fragment KFQ 37 (Déroche,  <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/QJQEKNSJ" sameAs="QJQEKNSJ" type="zotero">The Abbasid Tradition, London 1992</ref>, S. 84): "34 / Two folios / Mid-9th century AD or later / 11 x 15.5cm, with 4 lines to the page / <hi rend="italic">Material</hi> Parchment; the verso is the hair side / <hi rend="italic">Text area</hi> 5 x 11.8cm / <hi rend="italic">Script</hi> Close to style D.III / <hi rend="italic">Accession no</hi>. KFQ37 / <hi rend="italic">Another fragment from the same Qur’an</hi> / Istanbul Topkapı Palace Library, MS.B.3 / (Karatay 1962, no.47) / These two folios contain <hi rend="italic">Sūrat al-anfāl</hi> (VIII), verses 1-2. The text is written in black ink, with diacritical strokes, also in ink. Red dots indicate the vocalization. The end of every verse is marked by a 2.2.3c device.”</p>
            </summary>
